<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-12-23T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-01-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="269" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                            <head>269. Editorial Note</head>
                            <p>At a luncheon on March 21, President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>’s guests were Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName>, Foreign Secretary
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LSJSB1">Lloyd</persName>, Secretary of
                                State <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>, the President’s
                                Staff Secretary General <persName corresp="#p_GCAJ1">Goodpaster</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_DPH1">Patrick
                                    Dean</persName>, Deputy Under Secretary at the Foreign Office.
                                (Eisenhower Library, President’s Appointment Book)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>